      <abstract>The First Congregational Church in Argo, Illinois, was gathered in 1913 and
        construction on its church building was completed in 1916. The church underwent renovations
        in 1938 and in the 1960s with an addition to the church built in 1960. The church joined
        with the United Church of Christ. The church likely closed sometime between 2011 and 2018.
        This collection contains membership records, including baptismal and marriage records, as
        well as early records related to the formation of the church and the construction of its
        building.</abstract>
