    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Ladies Society of Argo was founded, with help from the Congregational Sunday School and
        Publishing Society, on May 5, 1911. From its formation, the goal of the Ladies Society was
        to form a church in the Argo community, which by 1911 had been anexed by the city of Summit.
        That effort had multiple starts but eventually resulted in the gathering of the First
        Congregational Church of Argo in 1913. Construction on a church building began in 1915 and
        the church dedication took place on May 7, 1916.</p>
      <p>The church grew during the 1920s and by 1934 the mortgage for the building was paid off.
        The church building was renovated in 1938. The church underwent another renovation in the
        early 1960s and an addition to the church to support educational and recreational purposes
        was completed on November 6, 1960. The church joined with the United Church of Christ after
        the denomination's formation in 1957. The church likely closed sometime between 2011 and
        2018.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains both administrative and membership records for the First
        Congregational Church in Argo, Illinois. The records include marriage records, baptismal
        records, membership records, remembrances, building records, an account book, a year book
        from the Women's Association, a church constitution, and a document declaring the formation
        of the church.</p>
    </scopecontent>
